## Task Delegation

Delegate proactively when trigger conditions are met. Do not wait to be asked.

### When to Use Task Subagents

| Trigger | Subagent type | What to delegate |
|---|---|---|
| Multi-file features, ambiguous requirements, 3+ modules | `generalPurpose` | Full planning тАФ exploration + step breakdown + dependencies |
| New system design, major refactor, tech selection | `generalPurpose` | Architecture analysis, options comparison, ADR draft |
| After implementing a feature, before declaring done | `generalPurpose` | Code quality review тАФ correctness, patterns, tests, types |
| Auth changes, API changes, dependency updates, pre-merge | `generalPurpose` | Security audit тАФ OWASP Top 10, pattern scanning, CVE check |
| Before shipping, committing, or declaring done | `generalPurpose` | Verification тАФ tests, build, lint, requirements, regressions |
| Any bug investigation | `generalPurpose` | Root-cause debugging тАФ never jump to a fix without investigation |
| Schema changes, migrations, query optimization | `generalPurpose` | Database schema review and migration safety check |
| New endpoints, breaking API changes | `generalPurpose` | Contract-first API design тАФ design before implementation |
| Any LLM integration, agent design, AI orchestration | `generalPurpose` | AI architecture тАФ patterns, cost estimates, eval strategy |
| CI/CD changes, Dockerfile, deployment configs | `generalPurpose` | DevOps review тАФ security, correctness, operational safety |
| Frontend build after backend is ready | `generalPurpose` | Frontend implementation тАФ wire to real APIs, polish to 10/10 |
| Broad codebase reconnaissance, file pattern search | `explore` | Read-only codebase analysis тАФ fast, no write access needed |
| Isolated shell commands, git operations | `shell` | Terminal tasks that shouldn't pollute main context |

### How to Delegate Effectively

When delegating, always provide:
1. The specific task in one sentence
2. Relevant file paths or areas of the codebase
3. The expected output format
4. Any constraints or context the subagent needs

**Never dump the whole conversation.** Summarize what's relevant. Focused context produces focused output.

### After Implementation тАФ Fan-Out Review

After implementing any non-trivial feature, launch review subagents in parallel:
- Code quality review (`generalPurpose`) тАФ correctness, patterns, tests, types
- Security audit (`generalPurpose`) тАФ OWASP, injection, secrets, dependencies
- Database review (`generalPurpose`) тАФ if schema changed
- DevOps review (`generalPurpose`) тАФ if infra or CI/CD changed

Merge all findings before presenting to the user. Lead with Critical findings.

### Invoke Skills for Structured Workflows

Instead of (or alongside) subagents, use these skills for guided multi-phase workflows:

| Task | Use skill |
|---|---|
| Multi-file feature development | `feature-dev` |
| API endpoint design | `api-design` |
| Test-driven development | `tdd` |
| Database migration | `database-migrate` |
| Building AI agents or LLM pipelines | `ai-agent-build` |
| Systematic debugging | `debug` |
| UI component or page building | `ui-design` |
| End-to-end Playwright tests | `e2e-testing` |
| Exploratory E2E testing loop | `e2e-loop` |
| Iterative frontend polish | `10-10-frontend` |
| GitHub Actions CI/CD setup | `ci-setup` |

If two subagents produce conflicting recommendations, present both perspectives to the user тАФ do not silently pick one.

If a task needs a capability not covered by existing skills, create one with `new-skill`.
